DOC.brief_summary: The primary objective is to determine if the weight gain of healthy term infants fed a commercially available term infant formula supplemented with DHASCO® is similar to that of infants fed the same formula supplemented with a new product, DHASCO®-B.
DOC.brief_title: Growth of Healthy Term Infants Fed Formula Containing DHA-B
DOC.criteria: full term infant (gestational age 3742 weeks) birth weight > or equal to 2500 g singleton infant < or equal to 14 days of age in good health parent must be >21 years of age parental consent congenital malformation or genetic disorder metabolic anomalies maternal infectious diseases, alcoholism, substance abuse mothers with gestational diabetes participation in another clinical study
